<h2 id="browser-information">Browser information</h2>

<p><em>Note: Update this section with compatibility for PennController 1.8</em></p>

<p>PennController 1.2 is compatible with:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new/">Firefox</a> (desktop)</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.google.com/chrome/">Chrome</a> (desktop)</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.apple.com/safari/">Safari</a> (desktop)</li>
</ul>

<p>PennController 1.2 is not compatible with:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Internet Explorer</li>
  <li>Edge</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h2 id="creating-account">What is the PCIbex Farm?</h2>

<p>The <a href="https://expt.pcibex.net/">PCIbex Farm</a> provides free hosting for PennController experiments.</p>

<p>You can create and host experiments on the PCIbex Farm by creating an account:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Go to the <a href="https://expt.pcibex.net/login">PCIbex Farm account creation page</a>.</li>
  <li>In the â€œNew userâ€ box, enter the following information:
    <ul>
      <li>In the â€œUsernameâ€ field, enter the username that you want for your account.</li>
      <li>In the â€œPasswordâ€ field, enter the password that you want for your account.</li>
      <li>In the â€œVerify password fieldâ€, re-enter the password that you used in the â€œPasswordâ€ field.</li>
      <li>(<em>Optional</em>) In the â€œEmailâ€ field, enter the email that you want to link your acccount to. PCIbex Farm does not share your email, and only sends emails for password retrieval purposes.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Click <strong>Create account</strong>.</li>
</ol>

